thread.title: School volleyball: Andover edges Barnstable in battle of titans
thread.title_full: School volleyball: Andover edges Barnstable in battle of titans

author: Cape Cod Times sports@capecodonline.com
title: School volleyball: Andover edges Barnstable in battle of titans
text: Posted Oct. 6, 2015 at 9:51 PM By Cape Cod Times Posted Oct. 6, 2015 at 9:51 PM » Social News ANDOVER - Madison Sollows and Riley James combined 34 kills and 32 digs, but No. 3 Barnstable fell to top-ranked Andover on Tuesday evening. Andover won 25-17, 21-25, 25-21, 16-25, 15-11. Andover (9-0) finished second in the 2014 Division 1 state tournament, losing in the championship to Newton North, which eliminated Barnstable (8-1) in the state semifinals. Barnstable hosts Newton North, the No. 2 team in Division 1, on Friday Michaela Cornwall had 10 kills for Barnstable, and Sara Higgins had 12 service points and two aces. Danielle Derosier had 10 service points and 36 digs, and Savannah Halperin had 10 digs. James also had 13 service points. Sollows kicked in eight digs. Ashley McCarthy anchored the offense with 36 assists, adding eight digs on defense. Caroline Brodt had 11 assists. Falmouth 3, Nauset 0: Kerry Shanahan recorded 18 digs and five aces help the Clippers get their first win of the season, topping the Warriors in Falmouth. Falmouth won 25-15, 25-13, 25-12 against their Atlantic Coast League foe. Natalie Gagnon had six kills and four blocks for Falmouth (1-7, 1-3 ACL). Paige Meade had 10 assists, and Caitlin Cavossa had four digs. Nauset fell to 3-7 and remains winless in the ACL. Both teams are back in action Thursday, with the Warriors at D-Y and the Clippers hosting Falmouth. St. John Paul II 3, Sturgis West 1: After dropping the first game to the Navigators, the Lions bounced back and ran off three straight winning games to clinch the victory at the Hyannis Youth & Community Center. Sturgis West (0-7) took the opening game, 25-23 before falling to St. John Paul II (7-5) in the next three games, 25-22, 25-22 and 25-15. The Lions had a number of solid efforts led by Kaia Whiteley’s eight kills and three blocks. Kyra McCabe had six kills and a block while Kali Tanguay chipped in with three kills and 13 digs. Also playing well for the winners was Alison Santos, who recorded four service aces and eight digs and Casey Sullivan with two aces and seven digs. Sturgis East 3, Cape Tech 0: The Storm used strong team play and serving en route to a win over the Crusaders 25-8, 25-14, 25-11 in Harwich. Lauren Bourgeous and Katrina Jackson led the way at the service line for Sturgis East (9-1, 4-0 Cape & Islands), with Emma Esterman and Colleen Cameron sparking strong defensive play by the Storm. Ashley DaCruz and Jill Doyle were also key for Sturgis East in the win. Cape Tech is 1-4. Upper Cape 3, South Shore Voke 1: Jillian Lizotte had 22 service points and three aces to lead the Rams past the Vikings in a Mayflower Small match in Hanover. Upper Cape won 24-26, 25-10, 25-15, 25-23. Molly Horn followed had 15 service points and an ace for UCT (7-5, 4-1 MAC-Small). Erika Kelley chipped in four kills and six tips, and Alexandra Hill had seven hits and three blocks. UCT hosts Norfolk Aggie at home on Thursday. By Cape Cod Times
